LAGOS – As part of its efforts to equip youths, TimeOn Kairos Polytechnic holds its ‘Catchment Communities Awareness and Open House Campaign Event’, studio launching (TV, radio, and photography), 2022 JAMB registration and UTME informatics also bus-stop naming today, February 19. Mrs. Eniola Ogundipe, Registrar of TimeOn Kairos Polytechnic, in a statement said TimeOn KAIROS Polytechnic (TKP) and TimeOn Kairos Educational and Vocational Institute (TKEVI) are community-based higher institutions, with a track record of providing quality education needed in developing today’s youths for the boundless opportunities in the 21st century. Ogindipe said that the programme became imperative considering the institution’s commitment towards targeting young bright minds, especially residents within Alimsoho, Agege, Ifako and Agbodo-Oke-Odo axis with sound education and skills acquisition. Among the guests expected at the event, she said include: government officials, community leaders, school principals, religious leaders, youth representatives, students, Dr Titus Kolawole Oyeyemi, Founding President/Chief Executive Officer, African Foundation\Project for Peace and Love Initiatives and John Ekundayo Idowu, Proprietor of TKP, the Rector, among others. She added that the programme featured Community familiarisation tours on 17 and 18, February prior to the Grand Finale today at the TimeOn KAIROS Polytechnic premises.